nt based on the ip and for the commercialization of those productsby becoming a licensor brk hopes to attract licensees who are best in class in their particular niches in order to leverage its ip into more products than it could produce itselfthe refcam is proof of concept that the ip works and would be one example of a product that can be produced from the ip stated brian keasberry ceo of brk inc im sure there are others we havent thought of and this opens up the field for us to form partnerships with creative people in a wide variety of industries it also frees us up from being exclusively manufacturers – which ties up a lot of capital for a small companyfor products the company intends to develop itself – and it says its got some in the pipeline it will outsource the research and development to american companies with expertise in the field theres no point in our having an rd department inhouse when there is so much talent available in our backyard and our research on our ip is basically done keasberry further stated to that end the board of directors has been given and accepted the resignation of chris stramacchia as cto and director of brk inc with gratitude for services rendered chris was spreading himself too thin – going to games trying to develop new products and helping at the corporate level now he can do what hes good at – tinkering and inventing and if one of those new products is based on our ip then he can become a licensee for that particular productfurther to its new goal of becoming a licensor for the ip brk has decided not to bid on the  olympic games after further reviewing the commitment of resources necessary to satisfy all parties concerned it doesnt make sense for us to send a crew and equipment half way across the world for a oneoff opportunity explained keasberry the economics just arent there our focus now is on strictly growing revenuesbrk inc invites fans to sign up for advance notice of games featuring the refcam at wwwbrkincorporatedcomabout brk incbrk inc pink sheets brkk established in  is owner of the helmet camera patents that make the refcam possible with the acquisition of the live broadcast helmet camera patent brk is poised to enter sports marketing in a big way isee sports inc is a wholly owned subsidiary of brk incthe foregoing contains forwardlooking statements within the meaning of the private securities litigation reform act of  forwardlooking statements are intended to be covered by the safe harbor provisions of the federal securities laws forwardlooking statements often contain words such as will anticipate believe plan estimate expect intend is targeting may should poised and other similar words or expressions forwardlooking statements are made based upon managements current expectations and beliefs and are not guarantees of future performance our actual business financial condition or results of operations may differ materially from those suggested by forwardlooking statements as a result of risks and uncertainties which include among others those described in any of our other filings with the sec in addition such statements could be affected by risks and uncertainties related to i commercialization of our newlyacquired helmet camera ii continuing development and protection of our intellectual property iii unexpected industry competition iv the need to raise capital to meet business requirements and v our ability to sell our products in order to generate revenues forwardlooking statements are pertinent only as of the date on which they are made and the company undertakes no obligation to update or revise any forwardlooking statements whether as a result of new information future developments or otherwise any future public statements or disclosures modifying any of the forwardlooking statements contained in or accompanying this news release will be deemed to supersede such statements in this news release information on brk inc’s websites wwwbrkincorporatedcom does not constitute 